
# Windows Event Message Monitor extension

Windows Event message Monitor works with .NET Agent Extension Manager to capture and report specific windows event and the message associated with it.


## Requirement

.NET Agent Extension Manager \
The AppDynamics .NET Agent \
.NET 4.0 or later


## Artifacts
extension.xml \
WindowsEventMonitor.dll 
## Getting Started

#### Download

```http
  Download, unzip and copy extension.xml and WindowsEventMonitor.dll
```


#### Create new folder on .NET Extension Manager root directory

```http
  Create a new folder under Extension Manager root directory.
  We can name it according to type of events we want to capture, in this case we want to capture Event Message so WindowsEventMessageMonitor or simply WindowsEventMonitor
```

#### Copy files into Extensions

```http
  Copy extension.xml and WindowsEventMonitor.dll file and place in the new folder under <Extension Manager Root Directory>/Extensions
```

#### Edit extension.xml
Edit extension.xml to provide controller details and target specific events.

Provide controller user credentials. These are required for publishing custom events to the controller. For single-tenant controllers, use "customer1" for the account. Controller host/port are read from the Agent Configuration file (config.xml).

```http
  <controller-info user="username" account="customer1" password="password" />
```
